Initial ExPeCT Data Analysis, Subjective Focus

Bryan Stanfill
January 3, 2018

Questionnaire & Exercise Perspective Goals

  • To determine changes in lifestyle questionnaires at three time points

    • Stress
    • Depression
    • Sleep
    • Quality of Life

  • Compare the results of questionnaires between exercise and non-exercise participants at three time points

  • To determine the impact of patients' adherence to the exercise program on lifestyle questionnaires

Notes

  • Some participants have complete questionnaire results but were marked as EXCLUDED in the CTC master file (Exp023, G-011, G-018 and G-032). I excluded those participants from the following analysis.

  • These results are based on the updated data file “ExPeCT Sub Results Jan'18.xlsx”

Adherence to PA Guidelines

  • I used the reported overall MET hours per week to measure adherence to PA guidelines

  • Two people in the Irish group have a large impact on the model results

Adherence to PA Guidelines, Cont'd

  • I removed those individuals and fit the model again
  • With them removed, there is a borderline significant difference between the exercise group in London versus the other groups, though that's likely due to the small sample size in the T6, London, Exercise group

Analysis for Other Questions

  • Subjective questionnaires are difficult to analyze because of differences between individuals' baseline (a “7” to me may be your “5”)

  • Instead of analyzing the raw scores, I analyzed changes in scores between consecutive time points

  • To increase statistical power, changes in scores were categorized into increases, decreases and no change. A drawback of this is that the magnitude of the change is lost

  • I used multinomial logistic regression to estimate the probability of each type of change by location, group and time point

Stress Analysis - By Location

  • The bubbles represent the probability of each outcome, the color indicates which outcome is most likely

  • A positive T0:T3 values means the reported stress score increased from time point T0 to time point T3
